-X is equal to the result of a complex formula, taking into account weapon quality, condition, bonuses, your strength or dex, the opponent’s armor, and some other things. <br>
-If you have NO trains in your weapon at all, each swing may do 25% to 125% of X in damage.<br>
-If you have trained up to 2/3 of your level in your weapon, each swing may do 75% to 125% of X. <br>
-If you are trained up to your level, each swing may do 100% to 150% of X. <br>
<br>
1. Is this correct?<br>
